AB  - This article complements a previous article on government-controlled enterprises. It examines the struggles, bargains, compromises and foul-ups between those influential players who determine these companies' decisions and actions. The strategy of such firms is seen as a political resultant: to understand corporate behavior one must explain key individuals' motivations, their stakes and stands and one must analyze their relative power and the pulling and hauling that occurs between them.
